name: benzoximate
Reason: The basic unit for this compound is benzene, which has a melting point of 5.5°C. The presence of the oxime group (OC(=NOCC)) and the ether group (OC) will significantly affect the melting point due to the potential for hydrogen bonding and dipole-dipole interactions. The oxime group can increase the melting point by approximately +50°C due to hydrogen bonding, and the ether group can increase it by approximately +10°C due to dipole-dipole interactions. The chlorine atom (Cl) in the benzene ring can increase the melting point by approximately +10°C due to the electronegativity of chlorine.
